						               													<description>The gym neurons is a set of questions involving insight, memory or observation. The aim is to give the right answer as quickly as possible. The game takes place in three phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Round 1: This is the right answer to 8 MCQ (multiple choice) in the time allotted by the hourglass. Players who gave the correct answer earning units of &amp;quot;time&amp;quot; in the form of chips. At the end of the 8 questions, the player who accumulated the least amount of &amp;quot;time&amp;quot; is eliminated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2nd round: The remaining players are faced with a 7 QCM and Memo matter where they are to observe an image for 15 seconds and then answer a question. The correct answers give points and avoid penalties. The two players with the most points qualify for the finals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Final: The two players have 2 minutes to answer six questions of pictorial logic. The player with the most correct answers wins, in case of equality, is one who has accumulated the most chips &amp;quot;time&amp;quot; wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
